The paper discusses a novel approach to learn a GA's fitness function for automatic software program generation, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of a GA and selection techniques also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the complexity of the fitness function growing proportionally with the problem being solved, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL). The use of a search heuristic to improve the GA's ability to discover correct programs suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of the system being applicable to other domains suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a potential sub-category.
